	<fdd:notes>
		<fdd:general>Derived from a <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/dd318183%28v=vs.85%29.aspx">Microsoft developers page</a>: "The AVISTREAMHEADER structure contains information about one stream in an AVI file."  It contains an fccType element ("vids" in this case, for video) followed by a fccHandler element that "contains a FOURCC that identifies a specific data handler. . . .  For audio and video streams, this specifies the codec for decoding the stream."  This compiler has seen this string in an AVI file: LISTt  strlstrh8  vidsUYUV. <a href="../contact_format.shtml">Comments welcome</a>.</fdd:general>
